      "status": "done",
      "comment": "## AndersonDev Tunnel Removed\n\nDone. `AndersonDev` cloudflared tunnel deleted and cleaned up. yepanywhere stays running.\n\n### Add this to your `AndersonTech_LAN` tunnel ingress config\n\n```yaml\ningress:\n  - hostname: claude.andersontechsolutions.com   # or whatever hostname you prefer\n    service: http://10.10.0.109:3400              # yepanywhere on Ethernet (preferred, wired)\n  # fallback if needed:\n  # service: http://10.10.0.47:3400              # Wi-Fi IP\n```\n\n**Machine details:**\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Ethernet IP | `10.10.0.109` |\n| Wi-Fi IP | `10.10.0.47` |\n| yepanywhere port | `3400` |\n| Service protocol | `http` (cloudflared handles TLS at edge) |\n\n**Note:** yepanywhere ALLOWED_HOSTS is still set to `claude.andersontechsolutions.com` in the launchd plist (`~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.andersondev.yepanywhere.plist`). If you use a different hostname in the `AndersonTech_LAN` tunnel ingress, update that value to match — otherwise API calls will return 403.\n\nTo update the allowed host:\n```bash\n# Edit the plist key ALLOWED_HOSTS, then:\nlaunchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.andersondev.yepanywhere.plist\nlaunchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.andersondev.yepanywhere.plist\n```"
    }
